I wouldn't say that this is bad. Those schools are suffering from Trophy syndrome, where everyone gets a medal for participating. The higher difficulty means students who pass the class with a B probably know the material better than Stanford students who aced an equivalent class. The point of grades is to rank people, and you shouldn't feel too bad about a bad grade, but you should feel much better about a good one.
When you get out of school and find out employers don't care about GPA, you can look back and have a laugh.
